    <td class="rowodd" valign="top" nowrap><i>2007-08-16</i></td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top" nowrap>7.0</td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top"><i><a href="/account/profile.php?user_id=9284">Gerald Lai</a></i></td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top" width="2000">Full-line comments (lines that begin with &quot;--&quot;) are aligned with the very previous line only if a whitespace follows after &quot;--&quot;. In other words, the character that comes after &quot;--&quot; determines alignment.<br><br>This allows commented code to be distinguished from real comments.<br><br>Thanks to Christian Brehm again for the idea!</td>
</tr>
<tr>
        <td class="roweven" valign="top" nowrap><a href="download_script.php?src_id=7460">vhdl.vim</a></td>
